            <bioghist>
                <p>William T. McCall (1890-1979) was a Philadelphia salesman for Bausch and
                    Lomb.</p>
            </bioghist>

            <scopecontent>
                <p>The collection contains information on a correspondence course in personal health
                    taken by McCall. The course was put out by 20th Century Health Institute, Inc.,
                    with lessons prepared by John X. Loughran, Ph.D. There are two volumes with a
                    total of 52 lessons. Topics include colds, sleep, diet, complexion, hygiene,
                    foot health, ulcers, and cancer.</p>
            </scopecontent>


